<TITLE> RMG workers block Mirpur, Dhaka-Syl highway </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com) Readymade garment workers of Mirpur and Narayanganj demonstrated again on Wednesday demanding pay rise. Workers of Opex and Sinha Textile took position on the main road of Mirpur 13 at around 9am demanding the minimum wage of Tk 5,000 and attendance bonus. Traffic from Mirpur 10 through Mirpur 14 remained suspended during the blockade programme. Police charged batons and fired tear gas shells to disperse the demonstrators. Later the workers withdrew blockade from the road and took position in front of the factory. bdnews24.com Narayanganj correspondent said that workers of Arrow Apparels Anirban and Arrow Apparels Mohammadi blocked the Dhaka-Sylhet highway for two hours demanding a pay rise, grinding traffic to a halt. They also damaged a number of vehicles. The workers initially demonstrated inside the factories in Tatki area of Rupganj upazila, said Rupganj police chief Forkan Sikder. Later they took to the streets at around 11am. Police arrived at the scene at around 12:30pm and tried to bring the situation under control. The demonstrators chased away the law enforcers and hurled stones at them, he said. Police charged them with batons and drove the workers off the highway at around 1pm. About 2,000 workers are employed in the two factories, the police officer said. On Tuesday, workers of the Opex Group based in Mirpur and Narayanganj demonstrated over a similar demand. bdnew
